{"TopicId":177319,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"KSP Has lost its flipping mind.","CreatedByName":"GalbinusCaeli","CreatedById":167499,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T05:27:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GalbinusCaeli","CreatedById":167499,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T05:27:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am landed and stable on minmus, I either send my pilot on EVA, or just turn off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and my lander starts spinning and bouncing off toward the horizon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVideo here:\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#e6ecf0;color:#14171a;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ehttps://twitter.com/GalbinusCaeli/status/1025975403951742976\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FireKerb","CreatedById":176562,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T05:34:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe video is too grainy. Maybe send a picture of the lander in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s probably a bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-05T05:34:51Z\u0022 title=\u002208/05/2018 05:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 5, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by FireKerb\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystifeid","CreatedById":187479,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T06:09:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is possible pitch trim is on. Try cancelling trim with Alt \u002B X\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E negates trim which is why these things usually wait until after it is turned off before they happen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-05T06:18:20Z\u0022 title=\u002208/05/2018 06:18  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 5, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by mystifeid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T07:24:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree with mystifeid -- looks exactly like Alt-W pitch trim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T08:20:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223428037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177319\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533453887\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree with mystifeid -- looks exactly like Alt-W pitch trim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. I had one of those \u0027why is my rover turning left\u0027 moments a couple of days ago. It was trim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167499-galbinuscaeli/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167499\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167499-galbinuscaeli/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@GalbinusCaeli\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0are you sure you didn\u0027t have any trim set at the time? On PS4 I believe it\u0027s L1/R1 \u002B left stick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T15:03:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood point. I didn\u0027t notice that it was the console version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s definitely pitch trim. You can see the pink \u0022trim indicator\u0022 just before \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is turned off at the beginning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, it depends on the preset -- but clearing trim is usually the left bumper \u002B clicking the left stick (L3).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GalbinusCaeli","CreatedById":167499,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T15:37:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDidn\u0027t even know pitch trim existed!\u00A0 I\u0027ll see if I can turn it off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-05T18:19:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223428167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177319\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533483472\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167499\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GalbinusCaeli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, GalbinusCaeli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDidn\u0027t even know pitch trim existed!\u00A0 I\u0027ll see if I can turn it off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP UI feedback FTW!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GalbinusCaeli","CreatedById":167499,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-06T02:00:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup, Pitch Trim.\u00A0 Cleared that and I am good!\u00A0 Thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GalbinusCaeli","CreatedById":167499,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-06T03:01:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMission to Minmus with new lander completed, launched and returned to base.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-06T03:16:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease note that in the current patch for consoles -- if you decide that you don\u0027t like trim and aren\u0027t going to use it, you can disable it in the settings so it will never turn on by accident. You can do it on a per-flight basis, too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T19:21:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been playing (PC) since 2014 and don\u0027t know what pitch trim is...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably why my space planes never work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kryxal","CreatedById":102688,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T19:48:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrim is wonderful for spaceplanes, it allows for constant pressure on controls and gradual adjustments instead of \u0022all or nothing\u0022 deflections.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}